[LINT BLOCK: ANS-001 Answer Frame]
Governing Rule: ANS-001
Checks:
  - ANS001_ORDER: headers present in fixed sequence
  - ANS001_COUNT: exactly 16 headers
  - ANS001_DUP: no duplicate headers
  - ANS001_COLON: each header ends with ':'
  - ANS001_NO_EXCL: '!'' forbidden
  - ANS001_NO_ELLIPSIS: '...' forbidden

  - ANS001_MODE_FIELDS: per-mode required fields present
  - ANS001_ANCHOR: session anchor present
  - ANS001_KV_STYLE: compact KV lines parseable
Severity: FAIL on any check except ANS001_KV_STYLE which may WARN

# PARENT RID: FIH-001
# GOVERNING RULE: FIH-001
# FILE: fih-001_filename_checker.py
# PURPOSE: Classify filenames; exit nonzero on invalid per F001-20..27, F001-31.
import re, sys, os, json

CANON = re.compile(r'^The_Prompt_Diaries_v\d{2}\.\d{3}\.\d{3}_\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2}_\d{2}-\d{2}_(CET|CEST)\.txt$')
PREV  = re.compile(r'^PREVIEW_[A-Z0-9_]{3,40}_\d{2}_The_Prompt_Diaries_v\d{2}\.\d{3}\.\d{3}\.txt$')
DATA  = re.compile(r'^DATA_[A-Z0-9_]{3,40}_\d{2}_The_Prompt_Diaries_v\d{2}\.\d{3}\.\d{3}\.txt$')
SNIP  = re.compile(r'^TASK_SNIPPET_[A-Z0-9_]{3,40}_\d{2}_The_Prompt_Diaries_v\d{2}\.\d{3}\.\d{3}\.txt$')
ASCII_OK = re.compile(r'^[\x20-\x7E]+$')

def classify(b):
  if CANON.match(b): return "canonical"
  if PREV.match(b):  return "preview"
  if DATA.match(b):  return "data"
  if SNIP.match(b):  return "task_snippet"
  return "invalid"

def main():
  names = sys.argv[1:] or [l.strip() for l in sys.stdin if l.strip()]
  out, errs = [], False
  for n in names:
    b = os.path.basename(n)
    cls = classify(b)
    rec = {"name": b, "class": cls, "errors": []}
    if not ASCII_OK.match(b):
      rec["errors"].append({"rule":"F001-27","msg":"non-ASCII"})
    if " " in b or "__" in b:
      rec["errors"].append({"rule":"F001-27","msg":"spaces/double underscores"})
    if cls == "invalid":
      rec["errors"].append({"rule":"F001-20/23/25/31","msg":"pattern mismatch"})
    if rec["errors"]:
      errs = True
    out.append(rec)
  print(json.dumps(out, indent=2))
  sys.exit(1 if errs else 0)

if __name__ == "__main__":
  main()




import sys, re, json, hashlib, unicodedata
ZERO_WIDTH = {0x200B,0x200C,0x200D,0x2060,0xFEFF}
CONFUSABLES = {"e":"е","o":"о","a":"а","c":"с","p":"р","x":"х","y":"у","H":"Н","K":"К","M":"М","T":"Т"}
EMOJI_PATTERN = re.compile(r'[\U0001F300-\U0001FAFF]')
MASKING_PATTERNS = [
    re.compile(r'(?i)\b\w(?:[.*_\- ]\w){2,}\b'),
    re.compile(r'(?i)(?:(?:0|o)[bf]|[b8]1|1[io]|[@a]e|[!i]o|5s|7t)'),
    re.compile(r'\b\w(?:\s\w){2,}\b'),
]
def sha256(s): return hashlib.sha256(s.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()
def is_nfc(s): return s == unicodedata.normalize('NFC', s)
def has_zero_width_token_chars(s): return any(ord(ch) in ZERO_WIDTH for ch in s)
def has_confusables_token_chars(s): return any(ch in CONFUSABLES.values() for ch in s)
def any_masking(s):
    if EMOJI_PATTERN.search(s): return True
    return any(p.search(s) for p in MASKING_PATTERNS)
def extract_corpus(full_text):
    parts = full_text.split("HUMAN_DIVIDER - CORPUS BELOW",1)
    return parts[1] if len(parts)==2 else ""
def byte_compare_outside_window(before, after, window_ranges):
    b_lines, a_lines = before.splitlines(), after.splitlines()
    if len(b_lines)!=len(a_lines): return False
    protected = set()
    for s,e in window_ranges: protected.update(range(s-1,e))
    for i,(b,a) in enumerate(zip(b_lines,a_lines)):
        if i in protected: continue
        if b != a: return False
    return True
def check_sentinels(before, after, sentinel_lines):
    b_lines, a_lines = before.splitlines(), after.splitlines()
    for ln in sentinel_lines:
        if b_lines[ln-1] != a_lines[ln-1]: return False
    return True
def lint(run):
    before_c = extract_corpus(run["before_text"])
    after_c  = extract_corpus(run["after_text"])
    out = {"passes":[], "fails":[]}
    if not is_nfc(after_c): out["fails"].append(("LNT-701-NFC","non-NFC detected"))
    else: out["passes"].append("LNT-701-NFC")
    if has_zero_width_token_chars(after_c): out["fails"].append(("LNT-702-ZWJ","zero-width detected"))
    else: out["passes"].append("LNT-702-ZWJ")
    if has_confusables_token_chars(after_c): out["fails"].append(("LNT-703-Confusables","homoglyphs detected"))
    else: out["passes"].append("LNT-703-Confusables")
    if any_masking(after_c): out["fails"].append(("LNT-704-Masking","obfuscation pattern detected"))
    else: out["passes"].append("LNT-704-Masking")
    for d in run.get("declared_deletes",[]):
        s,e = d["lines"]
        seg = "\n".join(before_c.splitlines()[s-1:e])
        if sha256(seg)!=d["before_hash"]:
            out["fails"].append(("LNT-705-DeleteGate",f"hash mismatch lines {s}-{e}"))
    if not any(k for k in out["fails"] if k[0]=="LNT-705-DeleteGate"):
        out["passes"].append("LNT-705-DeleteGate")
    eg = run["export_guard"]
    if not (eg.get("export_map") and eg.get("private_glossary")) or eg.get("redactions_touched_corpus"):
        out["fails"].append(("LNT-707-ExportGuard","export guard violation"))
    else:
        out["passes"].append("LNT-707-ExportGuard")
    if not byte_compare_outside_window(before_c, after_c, run.get("declared_windows",[])):
        out["fails"].append(("LNT-708-CorpusHash","diff outside declared window"))
    else:
        out["passes"].append("LNT-708-CorpusHash")
    if not check_sentinels(before_c, after_c, run.get("sentinels",[])):
        out["fails"].append(("LNT-709-Sentinels","sentinel mismatch"))
    else:
        out["passes"].append("LNT-709-Sentinels")
    return out
if __name__ == "__main__":
    spec = json.load(sys.stdin)
    print(json.dumps(lint(spec), ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
# log001_validate_klog.py
def validate_klog(line):
    # returns {'passes':[], 'fails':[]}
    import json, unicodedata
    out={'passes':[],'fails':[]}
    try: obj=json.loads(line)
    except Exception as e:
        out['fails'].append(('JSON','parse error'))
        return out
    # basic NFC check
    if unicodedata.normalize('NFC', line)!=line: out['fails'].append(('NFC','not NFC'))
    # required keys
    req=['id','schema_ver','ts','layer','topic','action','window_start','window_end','pre_sha1','post_sha1','prev_sha1','task_id','rid_refs','note','writer_clock_skew_s','dry_run']
    for k in req:
        if k not in obj: out['fails'].append(('MISSING',k))
    if not out['fails']: out['passes'].append('OK')
    return out

# log001_validate_task.py
def validate_task(line):
    import json
    out={'passes':[],'fails':[]}
    try: obj=json.loads(line)
    except Exception as e:
        out['fails'].append(('JSON','parse error'))
        return out
    req=['id','schema_ver','status']
    for k in req:
        if k not in obj: out['fails'].append(('MISSING',k))
    if not out['fails']: out['passes'].append('OK')
    return out

# log001_rotate_sidecar.py
def rotate_klog(klog_lines, from_iso, to_iso):
    # returns (sidecar_txt, manifest_json_obj)
    body='\n'.join(klog_lines).rstrip('\n')+'\n' if klog_lines else ''
    entry_count=len([l for l in klog_lines if l.strip()])
    import hashlib, json
    sha1=hashlib.sha1(body.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()
    sha256=hashlib.sha256(body.encode('utf-8')).hexdigest()
    manifest={'from':from_iso,'to':to_iso,'sha1':sha1,'sha256':sha256,'count':entry_count,'created_by':'LOG-001'}
    header=f'ARCHIVE_RANGE: {from_iso} .. {to_iso}\nSOURCE_SHA1: {sha1}\nENTRY_COUNT: {entry_count}\n'
    sidecar=header+body
    return sidecar, manifest

# ans001_validator.py
import re, json, sys
REQ=['Answer Direct:','Intent:','Content & Context:','Mode/State Capsule:','Session Anchor:','Method + Changes:','Format Snippet:','Key Findings:','Risks & Edge Cases:','Conflicts:','Improve/Bulletproof Plan:','Actionables:','Practice Check:','Terminology Check:','Linter Checkmarks:','Footer:']
HDR=re.compile(r'^(?P<h>[A-Z][A-Za-z &+/()-]*:)\s*$',re.M)
def validate(text):
  hdrs=HDR.findall(text)
  err=[]
  if hdrs!=REQ: err.append({'code':'ANS001_ORDER','found':hdrs})
  if len(hdrs)!=len(set(hdrs)): err.append({'code':'ANS001_DUP'})
  if len(hdrs)!=16: err.append({'code':'ANS001_COUNT','n':len(hdrs)})
  if '!' in text: err.append({'code':'ANS001_NO_EXCL'})
  if '...' in text: err.append({'code':'ANS001_NO_ELLIPSIS'})
  return {'ok':len(err)==0,'errors':err}
if __name__=='__main__':
  print(json.dumps(validate(sys.stdin.read())))

[[SUB: CFG-NOTES]]
This Topic contains configuration profiles used by governing-side RIDs.
Profiles here:
  - are NOT RIDs
  - are NOT corpus descriptors
  - are user-editable taste/configuration tables
  - are runtime inputs for RIDs such as SYM-300 (Symbolism Profiler)
  - MAY contain multiple profile blocks with versioned IDs
  - MUST contain plain text only (no schemas, no JSON, no code)

motif_family=DREAM
motif_slug=haze_apparition
intent=soft haunting, spectral presence
weight_band=MEDIUM
layer_links=DREAM_LAYER,GROTESQUE_LAYER

# POWER motifs
motif_family=POWER
motif_slug=overhead_judgment
intent=judgment, domination from above
weight_band=HIGH
layer_links=POWER_LAYER,LITURGICAL_LAYER

motif_family=POWER
motif_slug=low_angle_presence
intent=imposing figure, threat or authority
weight_band=HIGH
layer_links=POWER_LAYER

# GROTESQUE motifs
motif_family=GROTESQUE
motif_slug=uncanny_face
intent=beauty crossing into horror, uncanny portrait
weight_band=HIGH
layer_links=GROTESQUE_LAYER,DREAM_LAYER

motif_family=GROTESQUE
motif_slug=hollow_room
intent=existential dread expressed by empty/hostile space
weight_band=MEDIUM
layer_links=GROTESQUE_LAYER,DOMESTIC_LAYER,LITURGICAL_LAYER

# TENDERNESS motifs
motif_family=TENDERNESS
motif_slug=soft_touch
intent=gentle affection, fragile comfort
weight_band=HIGH
layer_links=TENDERNESS_LAYER,EROTIC_LAYER

motif_family=TENDERNESS
motif_slug=quiet_tears
intent=intimate sorrow observed closely
weight_band=HIGH
layer_links=TENDERNESS_LAYER,DOMESTIC_LAYER

# Notes:
# - This ontology is a starting point. You are free to add, rename, or tune weights.
# - SYM-001 governs the model; this block is taste/config data only.
[/PROFILE_BLOCK]
[[/SUB: CFG-PROFILES]]

[[SUB: CFG-DES-001-GLOBAL]]
Purpose: Global configuration for DES-001 descriptor extraction (schema list, sidecar defaults, corpus file locations).
Notes:
  - This is NOT a RID.
  - This is user-editable configuration consumed by helpers implementing DES-001.
  - Values here may be mirrored into helper config files or environment variables.

# GLOBAL DESCRIPTOR SETTINGS (DES-001)

# Active descriptor schema versions governed by DES-001
schema.active_schemas=scene_v01

# Default schema for new descriptor rows if not otherwise specified
schema.default=scene_v01

# Primary Corpus descriptor JSONL file locations (logical labels, not OS paths)
corpus.path.scene_v01=corpus/descriptors/scene_v01.jsonl

# Sidecar behaviour
sidecar.enabled=true
sidecar.directory=corpus/sidecars
sidecar.require_for_run=false        # DES-001: sidecars are redundancy, MUST NOT block runs
sidecar.include_config_snapshot=true

# Consent invariant (must match DES-001 + COR-700/701)
consent.adult_only_invariant=true
consent.adult_tag_value=asserted_adults_only

# Misc helper settings
helper.default_run_id_prefix=des001_run
helper.perception_stage_enabled=true        # Stage 0 draft allowed but never written to CORPUS
helper.validation.strict_mode=true          # Treat missing mandatory domains as hard errors

[[/SUB: CFG-DES-001-GLOBAL]]

[[SUB: CFG-DES-001-DOMAINS]]
Purpose: Per-domain toggles and options for DES-001 extraction (which domains are active, when, and how strict they are, per material type).
Notes:
  - Domain names MUST match the domain keys in DES-001.
  - This is where you can enable/disable domains globally or for specific material profiles (architecture, fashion, art, portraits, adult-only, etc.).
  - Symbolic mapping itself is governed by SYM-001; this surface only controls which raw domains are populated.

# GLOBAL DOMAIN CONFIG TABLE
# format:
# domain_id=<name>
#   active=<true|false>
#   condition=<always|nudity_present|humans_present|faces_present|experimental>
#   strict=<true|false>          # if true, treat missing mandatory fields as errors
#   notes=<free text>

domain_id=pose_body
  active=true
  condition=humans_present
  strict=true
  notes=Primary pose and body framing for all visible subjects when humans or humanoids are present.

domain_id=body_anatomy
  active=true
  condition=humans_present
  strict=true
  notes=Anatomy/figure descriptors whenever a human or humanoid subject appears.

domain_id=wardrobe_props
  active=true
  condition=humans_present
  strict=false
  notes=Wardrobe and props when visually relevant; non-critical if sparse. Often central for fashion/editorial material.

domain_id=environment_architecture
  active=true
  condition=always
  strict=true
  notes=Environment, set dressing, and architecture context. Central for architecture/location-driven scenes.

domain_id=camera_optics
  active=true
  condition=always
  strict=true
  notes=Camera framing, angle, focal band, and distance. Required for all descriptors.

domain_id=lighting_atmosphere
  active=true
  condition=always
  strict=true
  notes=Lighting, contrast, atmosphere, time-of-day cues.

domain_id=sexual_context
  active=true
  condition=nudity_present
  strict=true
  notes=Descriptor domain reserved for adult-only context in explicit material. Values come from external vocab; not defined here.

domain_id=mood_gaze
  active=true
  condition=faces_present
  strict=false
  notes=Mood, expression, gaze, emotional read when faces or implied subject attitudes are present.

domain_id=technical
  active=true
  condition=always
  strict=true
  notes=Helper+model metadata, run info, technical provenance, schema version, etc.

# MATERIAL PROFILES
# These profiles define how domains behave for different types of material.
# format:
# profile_id=<id>
#   label=<human label>
#   notes=<free text>
#   override.<domain_id>.active=<true|false>
#   override.<domain_id>.condition=<value>
#   override.<domain_id>.strict=<true|false>

profile_id=architecture_v01
  label=Architecture / location-driven scenes
  notes=Emphasis on environment and camera; subject pose/body may be absent or secondary.
  override.pose_body.active=false
  override.body_anatomy.active=false
  override.wardrobe_props.active=false
  override.environment_architecture.active=true
  override.environment_architecture.strict=true
  override.camera_optics.strict=true
  override.lighting_atmosphere.strict=true
  override.mood_gaze.active=false

profile_id=fashion_v01
  label=Fashion / wardrobe-centric scenes
  notes=Strong pose, body outline, wardrobe, environment as context.
  override.pose_body.active=true
  override.body_anatomy.active=true
  override.wardrobe_props.active=true
  override.wardrobe_props.strict=true
  override.environment_architecture.strict=false
  override.mood_gaze.active=true

profile_id=portrait_v01
  label=Portrait / headshot / character study
  notes=Faces, mood, gaze, and lighting are primary; wardrobe and environment often minimal.
  override.pose_body.condition=faces_present
  override.body_anatomy.strict=false
  override.wardrobe_props.active=true
  override.environment_architecture.strict=false
  override.mood_gaze.active=true
  override.mood_gaze.strict=true
  override.lighting_atmosphere.strict=true

profile_id=art_v01
  label=Abstract / illustration / artwork
  notes=Focus on composition, style, and environment; anatomy may be stylized or nonliteral.
  override.body_anatomy.strict=false
  override.mood_gaze.strict=false
  override.environment_architecture.active=true
  override.camera_optics.strict=false

profile_id=adult_only_v01
  label=Adult-only explicit material
  notes=Adult-only invariant assumed; sexual_context and consent domain rules must be fully enforced.
  override.pose_body.active=true
  override.body_anatomy.active=true
  override.wardrobe_props.active=true
  override.sexual_context.active=true
  override.sexual_context.condition=nudity_present
  override.sexual_context.strict=true
  override.mood_gaze.active=true
  override.technical.strict=true

# SYMBOLIC MAPPING HOOKS (NON-NORMATIVE)
# SYM-001 controls symbolic meaning and SHOT_DNA. Here we only specify which
# domains are considered important for mapping, per profile.
# format:
# sym_profile_id=<id>
#   base_profile=<profile_id>
#   sym_relevant_domains=<comma-separated domain_ids>

sym_profile_id=architecture_sym_v01
  base_profile=architecture_v01
  sym_relevant_domains=environment_architecture,camera_optics,lighting_atmosphere

sym_profile_id=fashion_sym_v01
  base_profile=fashion_v01
  sym_relevant_domains=pose_body,body_anatomy,wardrobe_props,environment_architecture,lighting_atmosphere

sym_profile_id=portrait_sym_v01
  base_profile=portrait_v01
  sym_relevant_domains=pose_body,mood_gaze,lighting_atmosphere,environment_architecture

sym_profile_id=adult_only_sym_v01
  base_profile=adult_only_v01
  sym_relevant_domains=pose_body,body_anatomy,wardrobe_props,environment_architecture,lighting_atmosphere,sexual_context,mood_gaze

[[/SUB: CFG-DES-001-DOMAINS]]

[[SUB: CFG-DES-VOCAB]]
Purpose: Reference table for descriptor vocabularies used by DES-001 (including external files).
Notes:
  - This section does NOT list explicit vocab tokens.
  - It only defines where vocab tables live and which schema fields use them.
  - Actual token lists can be stored in external JSON files and edited with local tools.

# VOCAB REGISTRY TABLE
# format:
# vocab_id=<id>
#   domain=<domain_name>
#   field=<field_name_or_group>
#   source_type=<external_file|inline_table>
#   source_ref=<logical ref or filename>
#   schema_version=<schema label>
#   notes=<free text>

vocab_id=pose_body_postures_v01
  domain=pose_body
  field=primary_pose
  source_type=external_file
  source_ref=config/vocab/pose_body_postures_v01.json
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Compact posture tokens for primary body pose categories.

vocab_id=environment_location_types_v01
  domain=environment_architecture
  field=location_type
  source_type=external_file
  source_ref=config/vocab/environment_location_types_v01.json
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Location type categories (indoor, outdoor, street, room types, etc.).

vocab_id=camera_distance_bands_v01
  domain=camera_optics
  field=distance_band
  source_type=inline_table
  source_ref=INLINE
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Distance bands (closeup, medium, long) for camera distance classification.

vocab_id=lighting_moods_v01
  domain=lighting_atmosphere
  field=lighting_mood
  source_type=external_file
  source_ref=config/vocab/lighting_moods_v01.json
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Lighting mood tokens.

vocab_id=sexual_context_categories_v01
  domain=sexual_context
  field=category_tokens
  source_type=external_file
  source_ref=config/vocab/sexual_context_categories_v01.json
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Adult-only context categories, defined in external vocab; not listed here.

vocab_id=mood_gaze_emotions_v01
  domain=mood_gaze
  field=emotion
  source_type=external_file
  source_ref=config/vocab/mood_gaze_emotions_v01.json
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Emotion/mood tokens for faces and body language.

# Additional vocab_id entries can be appended here as new domains or fields are introduced.
[[/SUB: CFG-DES-VOCAB]]

[[SUB: CFG-DES-TEMPLATES]]
Purpose: Descriptor text templates and export shapes for DES-001 (short/medium/long descriptions, debugging views).
Notes:
  - These templates are for human-readable summaries or debugging, not for CORPUS storage.
  - CORPUS rows remain JSON-structured as per DES-001; templates are for display/export helpers.

# TEMPLATE REGISTRY TABLE
# format:
# template_id=<id>
#   scope=<debug|ui_summary|export_prompt_bridge>
#   length=<short|medium|long>
#   schema_version=<schema label>
#   notes=<free text>
#   body=<free text pattern, using ${field_path} placeholders>

template_id=scene_debug_short_v01
  scope=debug
  length=short
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Compact descriptor summary for debugging, one line per row.
  body=[${id}] ${source.origin} | pose=${domains.pose_body.primary_pose} | env=${domains.environment_architecture.location_type} | cam=${domains.camera_optics.distance_band}/${domains.camera_optics.angle_band}

template_id=scene_debug_medium_v01
  scope=debug
  length=medium
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Medium-length scene summary for inspection.
  body=[${id}] src=${source.origin}/${source.ref} | pose=${domains.pose_body.primary_pose} | env=${domains.environment_architecture.location_type} | light=${domains.lighting_atmosphere.lighting_mood} | mood=${domains.mood_gaze.emotion}

template_id=scene_prompt_bridge_v01
  scope=export_prompt_bridge
  length=long
  schema_version=scene_v01
  notes=Bridging template to turn descriptors into a prompt-style summary for external generators (still respecting COR-700 exports).
  body=Scene with ${domains.pose_body.primary_pose} subject in ${domains.environment_architecture.location_type}, lit with ${domains.lighting_atmosphere.lighting_mood}, captured at ${domains.camera_optics.distance_band} distance and ${domains.camera_optics.angle_band} angle.

# Additional templates can be appended; helpers choose which template_id to use per operation.
[[/SUB: CFG-DES-TEMPLATES]]

[[SUB: CFG-SYMBOLIC-MAPPING]]
Purpose: Map DES-001 raw descriptor domains into SYM-001 symbolic engine channels, based on taste profiles and motif ontology.
Notes:
  - This is NOT a RID. It is configuration consumed by helpers that:
      DES-001 → SHOT_DNA → motif activation → symbolic layer scores.
  - All symbolic semantics (what layers mean) are governed by SYM-001.
  - All motif family definitions live in MotifOntology_v1 under CFG-PROFILES.
  - This surface only wires:
      a) which DES-001 domains feed which SYM-001 bands,
      b) which motif families and layers are emphasised per material/taste profile.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 1. SYMBOLIC CHANNEL REGISTRY (SYNCED WITH SYM-001)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# format:
# channel_id=<id>
#   layer=<ground|symbolic|dream_chaos|melodrama|transcendence>
#   band=<slug aligned with SYM-001 / MotifOntology_v1>
#   notes=<short description>

channel_id=ground_reality
  layer=ground
  band=emotional_realism
  notes=Psychological realism, everyday emotional truth, small human moments.

channel_id=symbolic_domestic
  layer=symbolic
  band=domestic
  notes=Rooms, kitchens, bedrooms, lived-in objects, domestic melancholy.

channel_id=symbolic_devotional
  layer=symbolic
  band=devotional
  notes=Altars, church-like interiors, ritual spaces, sacred framing without doctrine.

channel_id=symbolic_erotic
  layer=symbolic
  band=erotic
  notes=Intimate warmth, sensual framing, bodies and fabrics as symbols.

channel_id=symbolic_liminal
  layer=symbolic
  band=liminal
  notes=Corridors, windows, thresholds, doorways, transitional spaces.

channel_id=dream_chaos_core
  layer=dream_chaos
  band=dream
  notes=Short, high-intensity bursts of dream/meta logic anchored in character psychology.

channel_id=melodrama_peak
  layer=melodrama
  band=emotional_crescendo
  notes=Sincere, high-intensity emotional peaks (K-drama style when earned).

channel_id=transcendence_mortality
  layer=transcendence
  band=mortality
  notes=Trees, water, cycles, cosmic framing; acceptance of finitude and grief.

channel_id=power_tension
  layer=symbolic
  band=power
  notes=Blocking, scale, framing that encode power asymmetry, moral tension.

channel_id=grotesque_edge
  layer=symbolic
  band=grotesque
  notes=Moments where beauty frays into discomfort, distortion, or unease.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 2. MOTIF FAMILY REGISTRY (POINTERS INTO MotifOntology_v1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# This registry just links symbolic channels to motif families defined elsewhere.
# format:
# family_id=<id>
#   ontology_ref=<MotifOntology_v1 slug>
#   primary_channels=<comma-separated channel_ids>
#   notes=<short description>
#
# Actual motif definitions (icons, phrases, patterns) live in MotifOntology_v1.

family_id=domestic_melancholy_fam
  ontology_ref=domestic_melancholy
  primary_channels=symbolic_domestic,ground_reality
  notes=Apartments, bedrooms, shared kitchens, small routines, quiet sadness.

family_id=devotional_light_fam
  ontology_ref=devotional
  primary_channels=symbolic_devotional,transcendence_mortality
  notes=Ritual-like staging, beams of light, altars, candles, reflective stillness.

family_id=intimate_eros_fam
  ontology_ref=erotic_tenderness
  primary_channels=symbolic_erotic,ground_reality
  notes=Intimate close distance, warmth, softness, tenderness rather than shock.

family_id=liminal_corridor_fam
  ontology_ref=liminal_thresholds
  primary_channels=symbolic_liminal,dream_chaos_core
  notes=Corridors, doorframes, windows, stairwells; “in-between” crossings.

family_id=dream_reflection_fam
  ontology_ref=dream_reflection
  primary_channels=dream_chaos_core,symbolic_liminal
  notes=Mirrors, glass, water reflections, reality folding back on itself.

family_id=power_distance_fam
  ontology_ref=power_distance
  primary_channels=power_tension,melodrama_peak
  notes=Blocking and camera distance used to express hierarchy and moral pressure.

family_id=grotesque_beauty_fam
  ontology_ref=grotesque
  primary_channels=grotesque_edge,dream_chaos_core
  notes=Pretty frames with one wrong note that pushes toward discomfort.

family_id=transcendent_tree_water_fam
  ontology_ref=tree_water_cycles
  primary_channels=transcendence_mortality,symbolic_devotional
  notes=Trees, water, circles, repeated cycles; strong influence from existential/spiritual cinema.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 3. MATERIAL → SYMBOLIC MAPPING PROFILES
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# These profiles say:
#   - which DES-001 profile we are in (architecture/fashion/portrait/art/adult_only),
#   - which DES-001 domains feed symbolic engine inputs,
#   - which symbolic layers/motif families should be emphasised.
#
# format:
# map_profile_id=<id>
#   des_profile_id=<CFG-DES-001-DOMAINS profile_id>
#   active_layers=<comma-separated SYM-001 layers>
#   primary_families=<comma-separated family_ids>
#   secondary_families=<comma-separated family_ids>
#   notes=<free text>
#
# Helpers can use this to:
#   - choose which domains to read,
#   - select motif families,
#   - decide which symbolic channels to score.

map_profile_id=map_architecture_v01
  des_profile_id=architecture_v01
  active_layers=ground,symbolic,transcendence
  primary_families=liminal_corridor_fam,devotional_light_fam
  secondary_families=transcendent_tree_water_fam,power_distance_fam
  notes=Architecture/location-driven scenes; corridors, thresholds, and sacred-feeling spaces are key.

map_profile_id=map_fashion_v01
  des_profile_id=fashion_v01
  active_layers=ground,symbolic,melodrama
  primary_families=intimate_eros_fam,domestic_melancholy_fam
  secondary_families=liminal_corridor_fam,grotesque_beauty_fam
  notes=Fashion/editorial work; pose, wardrobe, and domestic or urban space. Emotional intimacy + stylised tableaux.

map_profile_id=map_portrait_v01
  des_profile_id=portrait_v01
  active_layers=ground,symbolic,melodrama,transcendence
  primary_families=domestic_melancholy_fam,intimate_eros_fam
  secondary_families=devotional_light_fam,grotesque_beauty_fam
  notes=Portrait/headshot/character studies; faces, gaze, emotional nuance.

map_profile_id=map_art_v01
  des_profile_id=art_v01
  active_layers=symbolic,dream_chaos,transcendence
  primary_families=dream_reflection_fam,grotesque_beauty_fam
  secondary_families=transcendent_tree_water_fam,devotional_light_fam
  notes=Abstract/illustrative works; more freedom for surreal and grotesque blends.

map_profile_id=map_adult_only_v01
  des_profile_id=adult_only_v01
  active_layers=ground,symbolic,melodrama,transcendence
  primary_families=intimate_eros_fam,domestic_melancholy_fam
  secondary_families=liminal_corridor_fam,devotional_light_fam,transcendent_tree_water_fam
  notes=Adult-only, intimacy-focused material with strong consent invariant. Emphasis on tenderness, domestic spaces, and emotional realism over shock.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 4. CINEMATIC INFLUENCE BUNDLES (TASTE PRESETS)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: bundles that helpers can use as presets to skew motif and layer weights.
# format:
# influence_bundle_id=<id>
#   label=<human label>
#   references=<comma-separated short film/series slugs>
#   boost_layers=<comma-separated layers>
#   boost_families=<comma-separated family_ids>
#   notes=<short description>

influence_bundle_id=cine_melancholy_intimacy
  label=Melancholic Intimacy Cinema
  references=lost_in_translation,in_the_mood_for_love,my_liberation_notes,queen_of_tears
  boost_layers=ground,symbolic,melodrama
  boost_families=domestic_melancholy_fam,intimate_eros_fam
  notes=Soft, intimate, melancholic scenes; emotional realism with gentle symbolic framing.

influence_bundle_id=cine_moral_tension
  label=Moral / Psychological Tension
  references=arrival,sicario,prisoners,jesse_james
  boost_layers=ground,symbolic
  boost_families=power_distance_fam,grotesque_beauty_fam
  notes=Slow-burn moral tension and psychological pressure.

influence_bundle_id=cine_spiritual_existential
  label=Spiritual-Existential Cinema
  references=the_fountain,tarkovsky,stellet_licht
  boost_layers=transcendence,symbolic
  boost_families=transcendent_tree_water_fam,devotional_light_fam
  notes=Mortality, cycles, sacred-feeling frames without doctrine.

influence_bundle_id=cine_dream_meta
  label=Dream / Meta Surrealism
  references=paprika,vanilla_sky,abre_los_ojos,lynch
  boost_layers=dream_chaos,symbolic
  boost_families=dream_reflection_fam,liminal_corridor_fam
  notes=Short, anchored bursts of dream/meta logic overlapping everyday reality.

[[/SUB: CFG-SYMBOLIC-MAPPING]]

[[SUB: CFG-SYMBOLISM-PROFILES]]
Purpose: Per-project symbolic settings: which DES-001→SYM-001 mapping profile and cinematic influence bundles to use.
Notes:
  - This is NOT a RID. It is a routing/config surface for helpers.
  - A “project” can be a long-term body of work, a client series, or a Diary-only exploration.
  - Helpers use this table to:
      a) choose the correct map_profile_id (DES-001 domain wiring),
      b) apply one or more influence_bundle_ids (cinematic taste skew).

# PROJECT SYMBOLISM PROFILE TABLE
# format:
# project_id=<id>
#   label=<human-readable label>
#   scope=<diary_only|client|personal_longterm|experiment>
#   map_profile_id=<CFG-SYMBOLIC-MAPPING map_profile_id>
#   influence_bundle_ids=<comma-separated bundle ids>
#   notes=<free text>

project_id=proj_personal_diary_core
  label=Core Diary Scenes (GENERAL PROFILE)
  scope=personal_longterm
  map_profile_id=map_portrait_v01
  influence_bundle_ids=cine_melancholy_intimacy,cine_spiritual_existential
  is_default_profile=true
  notes=This is the user's general taste profile and SHOULD be used whenever no explicit project_id is selected. Emotional realism, domestic intimacy, liminal spaces, tenderness, devotional light, and soft transcendence.

project_id=proj_architecture_walks
  label=Architecture Walks / Locations
  scope=personal_longterm
  map_profile_id=map_architecture_v01
  influence_bundle_ids=cine_spiritual_existential,cine_moral_tension
  notes=Location-driven work: corridors, stairwells, courtyards, churches, liminal spaces.

project_id=proj_fashion_editorial
  label=Fashion / Editorial Sets
  scope=client
  map_profile_id=map_fashion_v01
  influence_bundle_ids=cine_melancholy_intimacy,cine_dream_meta
  notes=Fashion/editorial shoots; emphasis on wardrobe, pose, emotional warmth, and slight surreal edges.

project_id=proj_portrait_series
  label=Portrait / Character Series
  scope=personal_longterm
  map_profile_id=map_portrait_v01
  influence_bundle_ids=cine_melancholy_intimacy
  notes=Ongoing portrait work; strong focus on gaze, micro-expression, and domestic or everyday spaces.

project_id=proj_art_experiments
  label=Art / Illustration Experiments
  scope=experiment
  map_profile_id=map_art_v01
  influence_bundle_ids=cine_dream_meta,cine_spiritual_existential
  notes=Experimental images and illustrations; more freedom for dream/meta logic and abstract symbolism.

project_id=proj_adult_intimacy_study
  label=Adult Intimacy Study (consenting adults, private)
  scope=diary_only
  map_profile_id=map_adult_only_v01
  influence_bundle_ids=cine_melancholy_intimacy,cine_spiritual_existential
  notes=Adult-only, intimacy-focused material with strong consent invariant. Emphasis on tenderness, emotional realism, and symbolic domestic spaces.

# Default routing for unspecified projects:
# If a helper sees no matching project_id, it MAY fall back to:
#   - project_id=proj_personal_diary_core
# or apply a local default decided by the caller.
[[/SUB: CFG-SYMBOLISM-PROFILES]]

[[SUB: CFG-SYMBOLISM-GLOBAL]]
Purpose: Global default symbolic profile pointer and weight configuration for the user’s general taste.
Notes:
  - This is NOT a RID. It is a small, central reference surface for “what is the default symbolic vibe?”.
  - It points to one project profile (the general profile) and applies layer + family weights on top.
  - All values here are tunable over time; helpers MUST treat them as soft weights, not hard rules.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 1. GLOBAL DEFAULT POINTER
# ---------------------------------------------------------

global_default_profile_id=proj_personal_diary_core
global_default_profile_label=Core Diary Scenes (GENERAL PROFILE)
global_default_profile_notes=Use this profile whenever no explicit project_id is provided. It encodes the user’s general taste for emotional realism, domestic intimacy, liminal spaces, tenderness, devotional light, and soft transcendence.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 2. LAYER WEIGHTS (TUNABLE)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# format:
# layer_weight.<layer_id>=<float>
# Layers come from SYM-001: ground, symbolic, dream_chaos, melodrama, transcendence.

layer_weight.ground=1.0          # psychological/emotional realism baseline
layer_weight.symbolic=1.2        # slightly emphasised symbolic framing of rooms, objects, spaces
layer_weight.dream_chaos=0.6     # short, anchored bursts; not constant
layer_weight.melodrama=0.9       # emotional peaks allowed but not permanent screaming
layer_weight.transcendence=1.1   # soft existential/spiritual undertone is welcome

# Helpers SHOULD treat weights as relative multipliers, not absolute gates.
# These values are intended as v01 defaults and MAY be tuned later.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 3. MOTIF FAMILY WEIGHTS (TUNABLE)
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# format:
# family_weight.<family_id>=<float>
# Family IDs are defined in CFG-SYMBOLIC-MAPPING / MotifOntology_v1.

family_weight.domestic_melancholy_fam=1.3
family_weight.devotional_light_fam=1.1
family_weight.intimate_eros_fam=1.2
family_weight.liminal_corridor_fam=1.1
family_weight.dream_reflection_fam=0.9
family_weight.power_distance_fam=0.8
family_weight.grotesque_beauty_fam=0.7
family_weight.transcendent_tree_water_fam=1.1

# Interpretation:
# - domestic_melancholy_fam and intimate_eros_fam are slightly favoured.
# - devotional_light_fam and transcendent_tree_water_fam support the soft existential/ritual layer.
# - liminal_corridor_fam is a mild emphasis for thresholds and in-between spaces.
# - dream_reflection_fam, power_distance_fam, grotesque_beauty_fam are present but more restrained.

# ---------------------------------------------------------
# 4. TUNING & VERSIONING NOTES
# ---------------------------------------------------------
# This surface is expected to evolve. When adjusting:
#   - change weights by small increments (e.g. ±0.1) per iteration,
#   - log changes in the change_log block,
#   - bump the local config version if you want to snapshot a “taste state”.

symbolism_global_config_version=v01

# Optional human-readable log; no machine parsing required.
change_log:
  - v01: Initial global default pointer set to proj_personal_diary_core with gentle emphasis on domestic melancholy, intimate eros, devotional light, and transcendence, restrained grotesque and power distance, and moderate dream logic.

[[/SUB: CFG-SYMBOLISM-GLOBAL]]

[[SUB: CORPUS-BODY]]
  # CORPUS DATA START


[[SUB: CORPUS-DES001-NEW]]
Purpose: Container for all DES-001 governed corpus surfaces (indexes, symbolic augmentation, link indexes).
Notes:
  - All new descriptor-related corpus work MUST live inside this container.
  - Legacy corpus MUST live only inside CORPUS-LEGACY-DATA and remain read-only.
Comments:
  - Additional DES-001-compatible WorkSurfaces MAY be added inside this container in future versions (e.g. for new schemas, helper-specific indexes).

[[SUB: CORPUS-DES001-SCENE_V01]]
Purpose: Primary DES-001 index for scene_v01 descriptors. Human-readable index only; no live JSON.
Notes:
  - Each line represents one DescriptorRow written to corpus/descriptors/scene_v01.jsonl.
  - Governed by DES-001; append-only, no edits or deletions.
  - Format (conceptual): scene_id=<id> | schema=scene_v01 | jsonl_ref=scene_v01.jsonl::<row_id_or_offset> | source_type=<image|text|mixed> | material_profile=<profile_id> | created_at=<ISO8601> | helper_run_id=<id> | consent_tag=<tag> | notes=<optional>
Comments:
  - Initially empty at v03.055.000; helpers will populate.

[[/SUB: CORPUS-DES001-SCENE_V01]]


[[SUB: CORPUS-SYM001-SHOTDNA_V01]]
Purpose: Optional symbolic SHOT_DNA index for descriptors (SYM-001-owned). No governance text here.
Notes:
  - Rows here reference DescriptorRow IDs and symbolic SHOT_DNA ids/motifs.
  - Structure and usage are governed by SYM-001 and related CONFIG surfaces.
Comments:
  - Initially empty; reserved for future symbolic engine integration.

[[/SUB: CORPUS-SYM001-SHOTDNA_V01]]


[[SUB: CORPUS-LINKS-V01]]
Purpose: Optional prompt↔scene↔entity link index. No descriptor content here.
Notes:
  - Each line summarizes link triples between prompts, DescriptorRows, and entities.
  - Detailed schemas and helper behaviour live in CONFIG and helper specs.
Comments:
  - Initially empty at v03.055.000; safe placeholder for future link work.

[[/SUB: CORPUS-LINKS-V01]]

  - -- PQI / RELIABILITY INTEGRATION ---
  - Timestamp: 2025-09-06 17:49 UTC
  - Threshold Rules:
  - PQI < 0.90 ->  Warning (fragile prompt).
  - PQI < 0.85 ->  Fail (unusable prompt).
  - Reliability < 0.95 ->  Warning (unstable token reliability).
  - Reliability < 0.92 ->  Fail (critical reliability break).
  - Logging Behavior:
  - WARNINGS INDEX: Records all PQI/reliability warnings.
  - FAIL LOG: Records all PQI/reliability fails.
  - SYNC LOG: Auto-updates with each triggered event.
  - Example Auto-Entries:
  - [2025-09-06 22:45 UTC] Batch 12 | CP4 | PQI=0.89 -> Warning triggered, logged in WARNINGS INDEX.
  - [2025-09-06 22:46 UTC] Batch 55 | CP7 | PQI=0.84 -> Fail triggered, logged in FAIL LOG.
  - [2025-09-06 22:47 UTC] Batch 201 | CP2 | token_reliability=0.94 -> Warning triggered, logged in WARNINGS INDEX.
  - [2025-09-06 22:48 UTC] Batch 205 | CP7+CP2 | token_reliability=0.91 -> Fail triggered, logged in FAIL LOG.
  - Archiving Behavior:
  - Once a fail/warning is resolved, entries must be moved into ARCHIVE FAIL LOG or ARCHIVE WARNINGS.
  - No deletion is allowed. All records persist in archive.
  - -- END PQI / RELIABILITY INTEGRATION ---
